1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.333
Knox cloud services 26.06 release highlights.

2
00:00:03.566 --> 00:00:05.938
Here's what's new in Knox Mobile Enrollment.

3
00:00:05.939 --> 00:00:08.066
View automatic enrollment status.

4
00:00:08.400 --> 00:00:12.308
This release provides the ability to quickly view whether automatic enrollment

5
00:00:12.308 --> 00:00:16.799
is enabled for your devices, letting you know if they will enroll in an EMM, 

6
00:00:17.033 --> 00:00:18.333
Knox E-FOTA,

7
00:00:18.533 --> 00:00:21.166
or Knox Asset Intelligence during device setup.

8
00:00:21.533 --> 00:00:26.502
On the Devices page, youll see new columns for the services that support this feature.

9
00:00:26.503 --> 00:00:31.466
These same columns will also appear when assigning enrollment profiles to your devices.

10
00:00:32.400 --> 00:00:34.794
Here's what's new in Knox E-FOTA.

11
00:00:34.794 --> 00:00:37.799
Automatic firmware installation when campaign ends.

12
00:00:38.433 --> 00:00:41.741
This release introduces the ability to automatically install 

13
00:00:41.741 --> 00:00:43.566
firmware at the end of a campaign,

14
00:00:43.566 --> 00:00:47.950
ensuring all devices update to the target firmware without manual intervention.

15
00:00:47.951 --> 00:00:51.297
You can find this new feature on the campaign creation page 

16
00:00:51.297 --> 00:00:53.665
after selecting a campaign start and end date.

17
00:00:54.300 --> 00:00:57.280
Here's what's new in Knox Asset Intelligence.

18
00:00:57.280 --> 00:01:00.732
New snapshot trigger for weak mobile network conditions.

19
00:01:00.732 --> 00:01:04.711
A new trigger option is added to the Schedule device snapshot feature, 

20
00:01:04.711 --> 00:01:09.265
letting you capture a snapshot when the devices mobile network is weak or unstable.

21
00:01:10.200 --> 00:01:12.970
After capture, you can view information about your devices 

22
00:01:12.970 --> 00:01:15.199
mobile network health in the snapshot details, 

23
00:01:15.666 --> 00:01:19.632
or export the snapshot in JSON format for further troubleshooting.

24
00:01:20.100 --> 00:01:22.500
What's new with Knox Remote Support.

25
00:01:22.500 --> 00:01:24.766
Send access code through email.

26
00:01:24.766 --> 00:01:28.766
Previously, initiating a remote support session required sending

27
00:01:28.766 --> 00:01:32.520
the access code to device users exclusively through SMS. 

28
00:01:32.520 --> 00:01:35.919
With this release, you now have the option to send the access code 

29
00:01:35.920 --> 00:01:39.033
to device users and other IT admins via email.

30
00:01:39.033 --> 00:01:41.570
The email will include the unique access code, 

31
00:01:41.570 --> 00:01:44.999
as well as QR codes enabling recipients to join the remote session, 

32
00:01:45.233 --> 00:01:46.366
download the agent, 

33
00:01:46.533 --> 00:01:49.099
or access the Knox Remote Support documentation.

34
00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:54.133
To learn more about the features in this release, or to get additional help at any time,

35
00:01:54.533 --> 00:01:57.699
see our documentation at docs.samsungknox.com. 

36
00:01:58.033 --> 00:01:59.199
Thanks for watching!

